Rock, Paper, Scissors Game in Java

This project is a simple implementation of the classic "Rock, Paper, Scissors" game in Java. 
The user competes against the computer, selecting one of the three choices: Rock (R), Paper (P), or Scissors (S). 
The computer randomly selects one of these choices, and the winner is determined based on the rules of the game.

## Features
-------------
- User selects Rock, Paper, or Scissors.
- The computer randomly selects one of the choices.
- The winner is determined based on the rules:
  - Rock beats Scissors.
  - Scissors beats Paper.
  - Paper beats Rock.
- Displays the result of the game (user wins, computer wins, or it's a tie).
- Asks if the user wants to play again after each round.

## Technologies Used
---------------------
- Java

